 are push-pull digital making TXS-class shifters the correct bridge to 3.3V MCUs#{11}":[45,46]},"outlinks":[{"title":"shields","target":"shields","line":7},{"title":"actuators","target":"actuators","line":8},{"title":"eda-fundamentals","target":"eda-fundamentals","line":9},{"title":"hall-sensor-open-collector-outputs-need-pull-up-resistors-and-produce-gray-code-not-binary-position","target":"hall-sensor-open-collector-outputs-need-pull-up-resistors-and-produce-gray-code-not-binary-position","line":18},{"title":"bss138-switching-speed-caps-at-400khz-making-it-unsuitable-for-fast-spi-and-high-speed-push-pull-signals","target":"bss138-switching-speed-caps-at-400khz-making-it-unsuitable-for-fast-spi-and-high-speed-push-pull-signals","line":22},{"title":"signal-topology-not-voltage-alone-determines-level-shifter-selection","target":"signal-topology-not-voltage-alone-determines-level-shifter-selection","line":22},{"title":"txs0108e-8-channel-bidirectional-level-shifter-auto-direction","target":"txs0108e-8-channel-bidirectional-level-shifter-auto-direction","line":32},{"title":"hall-sensor-open-collector-outputs-need-pull-up-resistors-and-produce-gray-code-not-binary-position","target":"hall-sensor-open-collector-outputs-need-pull-up-resistors-and-produce-gray-code-not-binary-position","line":35},{"title":"signal-topology-not-voltage-alone-determines-level-shifter-selection","target":"signal-topology-not-voltage-alone-determines-level-shifter-selection","line":36},{"title":"active-level-shifters-use-one-shot-edge-accelerators-to-drive-rising-edges-breaking-the-bss138-rc-ceiling","target":"active-level-shifters-use-one-shot-edge-accelerators-to-drive-rising-edges-breaking-the-bss138-rc-ceiling","line":37},{"title":"open-drain-protocols-require-pull-up-based-level-shifters-because-auto-direction-sensors-cannot-distinguish-driver-from-pull-up","target":"open-drain-protocols-require-pull-up-based-level-shifters-because-auto-direction-sensors-cannot-distinguish-driver-from-pull-up","line":38},{"title":"hall-sensor-wiring-order-matters-for-bldc","target":"hall-sensor-wiring-order-matters-for-bldc","line":39},{"title":"78l05-regulator-failure-kills-hall-power-making-motor-appear-dead-when-only-the-regulator-failed","target":"78l05-regulator-failure-kills-hall-power-making-motor-appear-dead-when-only-the-regulator-failed","line":40},{"title":"shields","target":"shields","line":43},{"title":"actuators","target":"actuators","line":44},{"title":"eda-fundamentals","target":"eda-fundamentals","line":45}],"metadata":{"description":"BLDC motor controllers like the RioRand ZS-X11H buffer the raw Hall-sensor lines through active digital logic and output push-pull 5V signals — not open-drain — which means bridging those outputs to a 3.3V MCU requires a TXS-class active shifter rather than the BSS138-class pull-up shifter typically used for I2C, and the topology of the downstream signal (not the upstream sensor) drives the choice","type":"claim","source":"docs/parts/txs0108e-8-channel-bidirectional-level-shifter-auto-direction.md","confidence":"proven","topics":["[[shields]]","[[actuators]]","[[eda-fundamentals]]"],"related_components":["txs0108e-level-shifter","riorand-zs-x11h","hoverboard-bldc-motor"]},"task_lines":[],"tasks":{},"codeblock_ranges":[],"key":"knowledge/bldc-controller-hall-sensor-outputs-are-push-pull-digital-making-txs-class-shifters-the-correct-bridge-to-3v3-mcus.md"},
